node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'UNILAD TECH The world must cooperate to avoida catastrophic space debris collision'.

node.text: More than 29,000 satellites, pieces of rockets and other bits of debris large enough to track from the ground are circling the planet and any one of them could bring the ISS crashing back to Earth 🌍🛰

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 14, 2021. May be an image of map and text that says 'here'samethane methane time bomb in Siberia warn scientists'.

node.text: Satellite imagery of northern Siberia show that vast stretches of limestone that used to be trapped under permafrost are emerging and thawing out, which could release a lot of harmful methane 🌍👀

node.text: Building the ultimate custom hot tub in your back yard 🛠🙌

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'UNILAD TECH >Bacel Paris to Berlin journey will take an hour with Hyperloop'.

node.text: Aviation is a significant contributor to the world’s emissions and the climate crisis. Trains are a great alternative but for most trips they are far too slow. Hyperloop hopes to solve that by the year 2045 🚄

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 13, 2021. May be an image of money and text that says 'UNILAD TECH The family that bet everything on Bitcoin whenit was $900 store earnings in secret vaults on four different continents'.

node.text: Didi Taihuttu, his wife and three kids liquidated all of their assets to buy bitcoin back when it was trading at around $900, today it's trading at over $45k 💰💰

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by UNILAD Tech on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'News Humans used up the Earth's available renewable esources for the year by July 29'.

node.text: Earth Overshoot Day marks the date when humanity’s demand for ecological resources and services in a given year exceeds what Earth can regenerate in that year. In 2021, it fell on July 29. 🌍😬

node.text: The IBM Personal Computer (model 5150, commonly known as the IBM PC) was the first computer released in the IBM PC model line and pretty much changed the course of computing forever. 💻🙌

node.text: Synchron has been granted regulatory approval from the FDA for its Stentrode device. It could allow doctors to treat conditions ranging from Parkinson’s disease to paralysis 🧠🙌
